50|$|The <b>European</b> <b>Patent</b> Office is {{directed}} by a president, {{who is responsible for}} its activities to the Administrative Council. The president also represents the <b>European</b> <b>Patent</b> Organisation. The president has therefore a dual role: representative of the <b>European</b> <b>Patent</b> Organisation and head of the <b>European</b> <b>Patent</b> Office. The President of the <b>European</b> <b>Patent</b> Office is appointed by the Administrative Council. A majority of three-quarters of the votes of the Contracting States represented and voting in the Administrative Council is required for the appointment of the President.|$|R
